1. 

General

. A deposit broker is any person in the business of placing or facilitating the placement of deposits in an institution,
as defined by the Federal Deposit Insurance Act 
(12 U.S.C. 29(g)). 


(n) Interest 


1. 

Relation to Regulation Q

