(b)(6)(iv) Renewal Policies 



1. 

Rollover time accounts. 

Institutions offering a grace period on rollover time accounts that automatically renew need not state whether interest
will be paid if the funds are withdrawn during the grace period. 

2. 

Nonrollover time accounts. 

Institutions that pay interest on funds following the maturity of time accounts that do not renew automatically need
